title: Séitifla
text:
Séitifla is a town in west-central <a href="Ivory%20Coast">Ivory Coast</a>. It is a <a href="sub-prefectures%20of%20Ivory%20Coast">sub-prefecture</a> of <a href="Vavoua%20Department">Vavoua Department</a> in <a href="Haut-Sassandra%20Region">Haut-Sassandra Region</a>, <a href="Sassandra-Marahou%C3%A9%20District">Sassandra-Marahoué District</a>.
Séitifla was a <a href="Communes%20of%20Ivory%20Coast">commune</a> until March 2012, when it became one of 1126 communes nationwide that were abolished.
In 2014, the population of the sub-prefecture of Séitifla was 93,430.
